Kevin Connolly: I'll try and bring that up as a follow-up.

22
00:02:37.320 --> 00:02:38.120
Sathya Narayanan: Thank you.

23
00:02:38.120 --> 00:02:43.020
Jeff D'Andria: The last bullet, application forms, Yeah.

24
00:02:43.740 --> 00:02:44.130
Kevin Connolly: Yeah.

25
00:02:44.130 --> 00:02:44.900
Jeff D'Andria: about that?

26
00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:49.030
Kevin Connolly: Yeah, that's just… in the age of AI, I do see…

27
00:02:49.170 --> 00:03:08.509
Kevin Connolly: So, like, typically application form will have your resume, but then there'll be, like, additional questions, right? Tell me a little bit about this. Maybe there's, like, two to three, depends on how they wrote it. Free-form text responses. In the old world, I used to index very heavily on those, like, I'd almost read them prior to even looking at a resume, because I want to see how people write and communicate and what they're thinking about.

28
00:03:08.530 --> 00:03:20.560
Kevin Connolly: And it is very common for candidates to just use AI to populate those. And what I think they don't realize is when you are reading literally hundreds of those, when somebody uses AI, even if they tell AI, like.

29
00:03:20.610 --> 00:03:29.109
Kevin Connolly: don't write it like ChatGPT. It's like, 200 other candidates also said don't write it like ChatGPT, and they're not good at how to do distribution generation, and they just, like…

30
00:03:29.650 --> 00:03:40.870
Kevin Connolly: it's very obvious, and I'm sure some people do use AI and get by without sounding so obvious, but, out of those, like, 1,500 applicants for a data analyst role, I can do very high confidence searches for, like.

31
00:03:41.200 --> 00:03:47.240
Kevin Connolly: fixed phrases that just come out of LLM, and probably reject 600 almost immediately.

32
00:03:47.470 --> 00:03:51.560
Kevin Connolly: You know, and it's like… Even if the rest of their experience is, like, legit.

33
00:03:51.800 --> 00:03:55.320
Kevin Connolly: I just don't want somebody… I don't want to hire somebody that's just, like.

34
00:03:56.320 --> 00:04:13.390
Kevin Connolly: half-assing their application, basically, or a startup, we need people that care, you know? So I… I think it's… and I have more on this, but I think it's really important for you to do research about companies and find one you genuinely care about, and then convey that you care about it clearly by writing, or take the time and…

35
00:04:13.490 --> 00:04:19.680
Kevin Connolly: I know it's a tough job market, so, like, empathetically, if you're gonna do 100 job applications, it's hard to do that for all of them.

36
00:04:19.730 --> 00:04:33.889
Kevin Connolly: Maybe you want to have some game theoretic strategy around, like, kind of lightweight, automated, almost, four of these, but, like, you should definitely find ones you care about, and my wager would be the ones that you care about the most are where you'll stand out, and you might get a screening call.

